[b]JMA Cluster Entries with Market Structure[/b] combines a 10-JMA cluster scoring system with full market structure context — Wyckoff phases, SMC Order Blocks, and a multi-signal entry matrix — to produce quality-scored entry signals.

[b]What it does[/b]

The core idea: JMA cluster alignment (how many of the 10 JMAs are stacked in the same direction) is a reliable measure of trend conviction — but it fires too often in isolation. This indicator layers it with structure context and a quality gate derived from historical signal analysis to filter down to the setups that have historically performed best.

[b]Signal components[/b]

[list]
[*][b]JMA cluster score[/b] — 0–100 alignment score across 10 Jurik Moving Averages
[*][b]Momentum[/b] — Short-term momentum confirmation
[*][b]Exhaustion filter[/b] — Avoids entries at momentum extremes
[*][b]Market structure[/b] — Wyckoff phase/event detection and SMC Order Block system (BOS, displacement, scoring, mitigation tracking)
[*][b]Quality scoring[/b] — Data-driven gate derived from analysis of 12,648 historical signals across timeframes
[/list]

[b]Timeframe presets[/b]

Lookbacks and parameters are automatically optimized for 15M, 1H, 4H, Daily, and Weekly charts. A dual-pivot system provides both live-ready and confirmed entry variants.

